reviewText: this film became of of my favorites in my (currant) top 30 films. based on another movie called THE MALE ANIMAL(which I have not seen yet so I can not compare.Burlesque dancer danced to save money for college. Her formal High School teacher is now a college prof, in lit. arts -writing and puts a play on each year. vIRGINIA MAYO and RONALD REAGAN are the two. They come up with a plan to write a new musical -for a college that does many the classics. All seems to go fine until another student spills the beans about the formal life. there is a lot more to it, but saying too much will spoil it.great dance numbers throughout the show with great supporting roles by Gene Nelson, Don DeFore, Phyllis Thaxter, and Patrice Wymore. Some standout scenes is seeing Reagan "drunk" and jealous, and the dance numbers in the film. Its worth having because each star played it so well, it gives a happy feeling, and laughter to the end of the film.
Title: N/A

reviewText: The trite songs in this musical slow down what may have been a passable, if pedestrian, straight comedy. The songs and musical numbers save one are the height of mediocrity. A burlesque queen (Virginia Mayo) quits show biz to enter college and one of her professors (Ronald Reagan) helps hide her past. But when a malicious and jealous student (Patrice Wymore) finds out, she blackmails her. This film has some of the oldest college students I've ever seen including Gene Nelson who has the film's best number, an athletic dance number in a gym. Poor Reagan has an endless (it runs about 20 minutes) drunk scene and it's one of the worst acted drunk scenes I've ever seen, I just cringed for the poor guy. Phyllis Thaxter as Reagan's wife and Don DeFore as her ex-boyfriend co-star.The Warners Archives DVD is a vivid transfer in its appropriate 1.33 aspect ratio.
Title: N/A
